<h2>2. Methodology Appendix</h2>
<p>
The findings in the indexed exhibits were produced by Recupero's deterministic
on-chain tracing pipeline. The methodology is described below so that its
reliability may be evaluated and its results independently reproduced.
</p>

<h3>2.1 Data sources</h3>
<p>
Transaction data is read from public-blockchain explorers / archival APIs for
each chain in scope. Every fetched transaction is independently verifiable on
the public ledger by its transaction hash. No data is synthesized; addresses,
amounts, and timestamps are taken verbatim from on-chain records.
</p>

<h3>2.2 Fund-flow tracing</h3>
<p>
Funds are followed forward from the seed (victim/subject) address using a
value-directed breadth-first traversal. At each node the outflows are matched to
the inbound value (same-asset and USD-equivalent matching, including 1-to-many
peel/split detection) so the trace follows the stolen value rather than
unrelated activity. High-fan-out service wallets are followed by top value.
Dust and unrelated commingled flows are pruned before enrichment.
</p>

<h3>2.3 Cross-chain confirmation</h3>
<p>
Where funds cross between chains via a bridge, the source→destination pairing is
confirmed by the bridge protocol's own cross-chain identifier (order id /
message hash / deposit id) observed on both chains. A cross-chain edge is
treated as high-confidence only when this protocol-native identifier matches on
both sides; otherwise it is reported at lower confidence or as a heuristic lead.
No cross-chain destination is fabricated — absent a confirmable match, the trace
reports the hop as unresolved.
</p>

<h3>2.4 Attribution &amp; confidence</h3>
<p>
Address labels (exchanges, bridges, mixers, sanctioned entities) carry an
explicit source and a confidence tier. High confidence is reserved for a direct
authoritative label-database hit (e.g. an OFAC-listed address) or a
cryptographic identity match; behavioral inferences (clustering, mixer
demixing) are reported at low/medium confidence as investigative leads, never as
proof. Each labeled address records the basis for its label (glass-box
provenance).
</p>

<h3>2.5 Chain of custody &amp; reproducibility</h3>
<p>
Each fetched transaction carries an evidence receipt (the upstream response and
the time of retrieval). The analysis is deterministic: the same inputs and
configuration reproduce the same output. This pack was produced with software
version <strong class="mono">{{ manifest.software_version }}</strong>.
Configuration of record: <span class="mono">{{ manifest.config_summary }}</span>.
</p>

